{"key":"post-12660207","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12660207</id>\n<content>If you fail to mist enough, your substrates will dry out.&amp;nbsp; If you mist too much, they will waterlog.&amp;nbsp; It's a judgment and visual call that each grower has to make.&amp;nbsp; With experience, you'll develop a feel for just how&amp;nbsp; much.&amp;nbsp; A properly built shotgun terrarium will take care of fresh air exchange on its own, but there's never harm in fanning it out whenever you mist, which should be a light misting a few times per day, rather than one big soaking.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>12660190</prev>\n<first>12659274</first>\n<last>12660207</last>\n<when>1275323107</when>\n<utime>05/31/10 07:25 PM</utime>\n</post>"}